commit.message:
Remove unnecessary and broken cross-compile check.

There is no need to disallow use of the built library if it was
cross-compiled and the user is not, and the check is fundamentally
broken anyway, since it checks for a STREQUAL instead of matching
truthy with truthy and falsy with falsy.

Remove unnecessary and broken cross-compile check.

There is no need to disallow use of the built library if it was
cross-compiled and the user is not, and the check is fundamentally
broken anyway, since it checks for a STREQUAL instead of matching
truthy with truthy and falsy with falsy.

commit.message: Also replace @lib_postfix@ in pkg-config template when using Autotools.
Getting ready for 2.3
Intersect: update doc and renamed some internal routines.
Fix up documentation of Intersect class.
Getting ready for version 2.3
Intersect: better names for variables; reorder functions.
Replace egrep by grep -E
Work around C2664 errors in VS2015 + VS2017
Add cnt3 + cnt4 diagnostics for Solve4.  Fiddle with Solve2.
Intersect.cpp: Adjust the _dx constants.

Include the coincidence indicator in XPoint.

All function can now return a vector of coincidence indicators.  Change
output for IntersectTool so that first 3 columns are always, x, y, c.
Fix move in Nearest logic.  Make coincidence flag visible.

Update library numbers.

Incorporation of exact functionality into Geodesic and
TransverseMercator counts as the remove of an interface (at the ABI
level), since constructors now have addition (albeit optional)
arguments.

Fix problems with build on Mac.

This includes fixing a serious typo in Intersect::Solve0.  Remove some
debugging stuff, clean up IntersectTool man page.

N.B. previous commit 52f7a1534caa0e9520795b4d5e06d74ed6668ad7 undid the
GEOGRAPHICLIB_EXPORT shenanigans for GeodesicLineExact.hpp introduced
with 72272cc96ea1026583eb4dcfcf38f4597ffcc1ef.  These caused
complications with the merging of GeodesicExact functionality into
Geodesic.  So I fell back to the "#pragma warning (disable: 4251)" fix.
Deal with Windows warnings
Add Intersect class and IntersectTool utility from misc-papers.
"On auxiliary latitudes" accepted by Survey review.  Update refs.

Merge branch 'main' into devel
